# Orion Execution Progress Tracker

Based on [version_implementations.md](file:///d:/Projects/Orion%20-%20A%20Multiverse%20of%20Stories/docs/version_implementations.md).

Last updated: 2026-06-23

## Implemented

- Core Electron/Vite/React shell with custom titlebar, sidebar, routes, onboarding, and secure storage.
- Streambert source parity is present for playback sources: Videasy, VidSrc, Vidking, and AllManga.
- Home, Discover, Search, Movie, TV, Library, Downloads, and Settings routes are wired.
- Movie and TV detail pages expose visible download actions.
- Quick search now uses a dedicated command-palette overlay with stronger backdrop isolation and scroll lock.
- Home now exposes saved titles as a visible My List row.
- Library now has Continue / My List / History tabs with compact, consistent card grids.
- Sidebar now labels the saved destination as My Library, groups navigation into Browse / Personal / System, and uses a visible edge rail plus top pin control instead of the hidden bottom arrow.
- My Library/My List saved-count badges were removed; Downloads keeps an active-download badge only.
- Global media card sizing tokens now bound compact, standard, and collection cards so wide screens do not create oversized movie, TV, anime, season, library, or collection cards.
- Home My List now renders a compact shelf for 1-3 saved titles and a clearer "View all in My Library" path.
- Bundled TMDB token fallback plumbing exists through `VITE_TMDB_READ_TOKEN` / `VITE_TMDB_TOKEN`; user-configured tokens still override it.
- Settings and System Check now show TMDB token source as Bundled, User configured, or Missing.
- Home carousel cards were reduced slightly to lower vertical emptiness while keeping the cinematic motion.
- Movie and TV playback now scroll/navigates to the player when playback starts.
- Movie and TV player overlays now fade on cursor idle and return on interaction.
- TV episode cards now expose per-episode download buttons.
- TV episode cards received UI polish for alignment, selected/playing state, action placement, and cleaner expandable descriptions.
- TV seasons now expose a visible Download Season entry point that starts capture/download flow for the first pending episode in the selected season.
- Download backend now targets direct `yt-dlp + ffmpeg` instead of Streambert's helper-folder binary flow.
- Orion can detect downloader tools from PATH or its app-managed tools folder.
- Windows app-managed downloader install/repair IPC exists for `yt-dlp.exe` and `ffmpeg.exe`.
- Video downloads do not require subtitle API keys; subtitle APIs are only used when online subtitle search is enabled.
- System Check now considers Orion's managed downloader tools folder before PATH.
- Build verification passed with `npm run build`.

