## Known Limitations

- Download Season is not yet a true unattended bulk-season queue because Orion must capture a playable stream URL for each episode before yt-dlp can download it.
- Download capture recognition still needs backend debugging after the UI-first pass.
- The bundled TMDB token fallback requires the free token to be supplied at build time through `VITE_TMDB_READ_TOKEN` or `VITE_TMDB_TOKEN`; no real token is committed in source.
- App-managed downloader installation is currently Windows-focused. macOS/Linux users need `yt-dlp` and `ffmpeg` on PATH for now.
- Some older UI text/comments still contain mojibake from the source port; user-facing cleanup should continue during UI polish.
- Git commands currently report this workspace as not a repository even though a `.git` directory exists; verification used build/syntax checks instead of Git diff.

